    • Method Detail

      • getTopLevelCount

        int getTopLevelCount()
        Return the number of currently active Top Level Windows from all known Agents.

      • getTopLevelWindows

        java.lang.Object[] getTopLevelWindows()
        Return an array representing the TopLevel windows from all known Agents.
        Returns:
        Object[] representing all active top level windows in all JVMs. This array will be Server/Agent specific and may be nothing more than arrays of the hashcodes used to uniquely identify objects in an Agent-maintained Hashtable. A zero-length array will be returned if no Top Level Windows are active.
